		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Solar chimney</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<dl>
<dd><i>This article refers to a device for ventilation. For the power generation technology, see <a href="/wiki/Solar_updraft_tower" title="Solar updraft tower">Solar updraft tower</a>.</i></dd>
</dl>
<p>A <b>solar chimney</b> — often referred to as a <b>thermal chimney</b> — is a way of improving the natural <a href="/wiki/Ventilation_(architecture)" title="Ventilation (architecture)">ventilation</a> of <a href="/wiki/Building" title="Building">buildings</a> by using <a href="/wiki/Convection" title="Convection">convection</a> of <a href="/wiki/Air" title="Air" class="mw-redirect">air</a> heated by <a href="/wiki/Passive_solar" title="Passive solar">passive solar</a> <a href="/wiki/Energy" title="Energy">energy</a>. A simple description of a solar chimney is that of a vertical shaft utilizing solar energy to enhance the natural <a href="/wiki/Natural_ventilation#Stack_driven_ventilation" title="Natural ventilation">stack ventilation</a> through a building.</p>
<p>The <a href="/wiki/Solar_power" title="Solar power">solar</a> <a href="/wiki/Chimney" title="Chimney">chimney</a> has been in use for centuries, particularly in the <a href="/wiki/Middle_east" title="Middle east" class="mw-redirect">Middle east</a>, as well as by the <a href="/wiki/Ancient_Rome" title="Ancient Rome">Romans</a>.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
